HEADWORD: Ployment
<hw>Ploy"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>The act or movement of forming a column from a line of troops on
some designated subdivision; -- the opposite of
<xex>deployment</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluck</ent>⟦br⟧
